column1: types of nodes in wireless sensor networks
column3: A sensor node, also known as a mote , is a node in a sensor network that is capable of performing some processing, gathering sensory information and communicating with other connected nodes in the network.

column1: types of clustering in wireless sensor networks
column3: Out of these, clustering algorithms have gained more importance, in increasing the life time of the WSN, because of their approach in cluster head selection and data aggregation.
